    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-01-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1030"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1030">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">791.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/1–553:
                    Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-01-05">January 5,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Request under Section 408(<hi rend="italic">e</hi>) by the Government of
                        India for <gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss>–119G Aircraft.</item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_A1">A–</gloss>407. This subject was discussed during a recent
                    visit to New Delhi by Mr. <persName>Theodore Tannenwald</persName> who has
                    requested that the following information be conveyed to the Embassy.</p>
                <p>The Government of India requested, on October 1, 1952, a quantity of twenty-six
                        <gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss>–119G Fairchild aircraft including supporting
                    equipment and spare parts.<note n="1" xml:id="d1030fn1">See the memorandum by
                            <persName corresp="#p_MEM1">Martin</persName>, Oct. 20, <ref
                            target="#pg_1668">p. 1668</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>This request was approved by the Departments of State and Defense and on November
                    20, 1952 the Department of the Air Force wrote a letter offer to the Embassy of
                        India<note n="2" xml:id="d1030fn2">A copy of this letter has not been found
                        in the Department of State flies.</note> containing estimated delivery <pb
                        facs="0632" n="1682" xml:id="pg_1682"/> dates for the above mentioned
                    equipment in 1954 and 1955 at an approximate total cost of $24,247,964 based on
                    a January 1, 1953 acceptance.</p>
                <p>The Indian Air Attaché has indicated to the Department of the Air Force that they
                    plan to accept the offer and he has informally discussed financial arrangements
                    with the Comptroller, Office of the Director for Mutual Security. As of this
                    date, no formal acceptance has been received from the Indian Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
